TSMC’s Chang Says Weakening Economy Will Affect Chip Market

-- B y   T i m   C u l p a n
-- 
2011-09-02T08:56:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/taiwan-semiconductor-expects-weakening-economy-will-affect-chip-market.html
Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing
Co. Chairman and Chief Executive Officer  Morris Chang  said his
customers’ confidence in the global economy has weakened.  A weakening global economy will impact the chip market,
Chang said in Taipei without providing data. TSMC hasn’t revised
its forecasts and will update investors next month, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tim Culpan in Taipei at 
 tculpan1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
